{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "69eab449",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Underfitting "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c2291129",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "Underfitting happens when the model fails to learn important patterns. \n",
    "It performs poorly on both training and testing data. \n",
    "\n",
    "Underfitting happens due to:\n",
    "-Model is too simple\n",
    "-Very high regularization\n",
    "-Features are weak or missing\n",
    "-Not enough training\n",
    "-High bias\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ba752384",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Bias-Variance Inside Underfitting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "926d5195",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Underfitting mainly occurs due to high bias:\n",
    "\n",
    "-High bias means model makes strong assumptions\n",
    "-Ignores patterns\n",
    "-Learns an overly simple representation\n",
    "-Variance is low because the model gives similar outputs even if the data changes\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    " Underfitting = High Bias + Low Variance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c65c6cdc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Overfitting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3d99d193",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Overfitting happens when the model learns too much from the training data, including noise and outliers. \n",
    "It performs very well on training data but poorly on test data. \n",
    "\n",
    "Overfitting happens due to:\n",
    "-Model too complex\n",
    "-Too many features\n",
    "-Very little data\n",
    "-No regularization\n",
    "-High variance\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Variance: Error that happens when a machine learning model learns too much from the data, including random noise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7ee10077",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Bias-Variance inside Overfitting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "eedc70de",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Overfitting is mainly caused by high variance:\n",
    "-High variance means model reacts too strongly to training data\n",
    "-Learns noise as patterns\n",
    "-Low bias because the model is extremely flexible\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Overfitting = Low Bias + High Variance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5b015926",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Underfitting : \n",
    "Straight line trying to fit a curved dataset but cannot capture the data's patterns, \n",
    "leading to poor performance on both training and test sets.\n",
    "\n",
    "Overfitting: \n",
    "A squiggly curve passing through all training points, failing to generalize performing \n",
    "well on training data but poorly on test data.\n",
    "\n",
    "Appropriate Fitting: \n",
    "Curve that follows the data trend without overcomplicating to capture the true patterns in the data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a004f17",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Bias Variance Tradeoff"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f56e680e",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "The relationship between bias and variance is often referred to as the bias-variance tradeoff, \n",
    "which highlights the need for balance:\n",
    "\n",
    "-Increasing model complexity reduces bias but increases variance (risk of overfitting).\n",
    "-Simplifying the model reduces variance but increases bias (risk of underfitting).\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is to find an optimal balance where both bias and variance are minimized, \n",
    "resulting in good generalization performance."
   ]
  }
 ],
